lfc <- 2

PIWIL1 Knockdown Microarray

Cell Line 4121

#the design of the experiment. 
#12 samples from 3 cell lines and 4 repeats each
designArray=c(rep("shNT", 4), rep("shA", 4), rep("shE",4))
#designArray=c("shNT","shNT","shNT","shNT", "shA","shA","shA","shA", "shE","shE","shE","shE")
`cell_` <- factor(designArray)
design <-model.matrix(~`cell_` + 0)
rm('cell_')

#convert the probe data to an illumina ExpressionSet required for analysis
c4121_ES_AE <- createExpressionSet("../Experiments/Cell_Line_4121_AE/")
## Warning in readQC(file = qcFile, sep = qc.sep, skip = qc.skip, columns = qc.columns, : controlIDs non-unique: 4 repeated entries have been removed.
#mds Plot of the cell lines
#cell lines are placed based on typical distances of the top log2 fold changes
plotMDS(c4121_ES_AE, labels = designArray, cex = .7)

#doing a linear fit of the data
fit_c4121L <- lmFit(c4121_ES_AE, design)
#creating the contasts, the differences, between each cell type
contrasts <- makeContrasts(cell_shA-cell_shNT, cell_shE-cell_shNT, levels = design)
fit_c4121L <- contrasts.fit(fit_c4121L, contrasts)
fit_c4121L <- eBayes(fit_c4121L, trend = TRUE)


#find probes with at least 1 log fold change difference in shNT vs both shA and shE and put in a venn diagram
results <- decideTests(fit_c4121L[, c("cell_shA - cell_shNT", "cell_shE - cell_shNT")], 
                       lfc = lfc, 
                       p.value = .05)
#create a venn diagram showing the number of  up and down regulated probes
vennDiagram(results, 
            include = c("up", "down"), 
            names = c("shA-shNT","shE-shNT"))

#display the probes over expressed in at least 1 sample
significant_rows <- apply(results, MARGIN = 1, FUN = max) == 1 #find any probe that was over expressed in at least 1 sample
kable(caption = "Probes Over Expressed in at least 1 Sample", 
      row.names = FALSE,
      x = subset(select = -c(CHROMOSOME,ILMN_GENE,SEARCH_KEY, Status, P.Value, adj.P.Val),
                 x = topTable(fit = fit_c4121L[significant_rows,],
                              number = length(significant_rows)
                              )
                 )
      )

                              coef = 1, #1 is the E cell line

                       top_c3832L_BC,
                       topTable(fit_c3832L,
                              coef = 2, #2 is the E cell line
                              number = "all",
                              lfc = lfc, 
                              p.value = .05,
                              sort.by = "logFC"
                              , resort.by = "logFC")[,c("SYMBOL", "logFC")])
#removing probes with no gene symbols associated
top_c3832L_BC <- top_c3832L_BC[top_c3832L_BC$SYMBOL != "",]
#averaging the probes for the same genes
top_c3832L_BC <- aggregate(.~SYMBOL, na.action= NULL, data = top_c3832L_BC, mean, na.rm = TRUE)
colnames(top_c3832L_BC) <- c("SYMBOL", "3832_B", "3832_C")
#the design of the experiment. 
#12 samples from 3 cell lines and 4 repeats each
designArray=c(rep("shNT", 4), rep("shH", 4), rep("shI",4))
#designArray=c("shNT","shNT","shNT","shNT", "shA","shA","shA","shA", "shE","shE","shE","shE")
`cell_` <- factor(designArray)
design <-model.matrix(~`cell_` + 0)
rm('cell_')

#convert the probe data to an illumina ExpressionSet required for analysis
c4121_ES_HI <- createExpressionSet("../Experiments/Cell_Line_4121_HI/")
## Warning in readQC(file = qcFile, sep = qc.sep, skip = qc.skip, columns = qc.columns, : controlIDs non-unique: 4 repeated entries have been removed.
#mds Plot of the cell lines
#cell lines are placed based on typical distances of the top log2 fold changes
plotMDS(c4121_ES_HI, labels = designArray, cex = 1,2)

#doing a linear fit of the data
fit_c4121L <- lmFit(c4121_ES_HI, design)
#creating the contasts, the differences, between each cell type
contrasts <- makeContrasts(cell_shH-cell_shNT, cell_shI-cell_shNT, levels = design)
fit_c4121L <- contrasts.fit(fit_c4121L, contrasts)
fit_c4121L <- eBayes(fit_c4121L, trend = TRUE)


#find probes with at least 1 log fold change difference in shNT vs both shA and shE and put in a venn diagram
results <- decideTests(fit_c4121L[, c("cell_shH - cell_shNT", "cell_shI - cell_shNT")], 
                       lfc = lfc, 
                       p.value = .05)
#create a venn diagram showing the number of  up and down regulated probes
vennDiagram(results, 
            include = c("up", "down"), 
            names = c("shH-shNT","shI-shNT"), cex = 1.5)

#removing probes with no gene symbols associated
top_c4121L_HI <- top_c4121L_HI[top_c4121L_HI$SYMBOL != "",]
#averaging the probes for the same genes
top_c4121L_HI <- aggregate(.~SYMBOL, na.action= NULL, data = top_c4121L_HI, mean, na.rm = TRUE)
colnames(top_c4121L_HI) <- c("SYMBOL", "4121_H", "4121_I")
 #thedesign of the experiment. 
#12 samples from 3 cell lines and 4 repeats each
designArray=c(rep("shNT", 4), rep("shH", 4), rep("shI",4))
#designArray=c("shNT","shNT","shNT","shNT", "shA","shA","shA","shA", "shE","shE","shE","shE")
`cell_` <- factor(designArray)
design <-model.matrix(~`cell_` + 0)
rm('cell_')
